<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4254] BrokerXmlConfigStartTest fails intermittently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4254</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BrokerXmlConfigStartTest.testStartBrokerUsingSampleConfig fails intermittently on Hudson/Jenkins with the error &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Error creating bean with name &apos;Server&apos; defined in file &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;/home/hudson/hudson-slave/workspace/ActiveMQ-Java7/assembly/target/conf/jetty-demo.xml&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: Invocation of init method failed; nested exception is java.net.BindException: Address already in use&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a patch with this test rewritten as a JUnit4 Parameterized test. This creates runs each config as a separate test case and seems to resolve the broker start/stop issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
